==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''audire'' to hear; through Old French ''ouïr'' to hear; through Anglo-French.
===Interjection===

'''oyez'''

# Hear ye. Attend. (Called by public [[crier]]s or in [[court]] usually three times to secure silence). 
*Practise note: It is still used in the United State's Supreme Court, and in many state supreme courts, although lower courts seem to have dropped its use.

